{"title": "How's Your British Accent?", "content": "A British actor, living in America, is playing an American character on an American TV show. For this role, they learn to speak with an American accent, with varying degrees of success. Then, one episode, they are required to go undercover as a Brit and, would you believe it, they can do a perfect British accent.\n\nThis trope comes when a character has to assume an accent which for the character is fake, but for the actor is in fact their natural speaking voice, or at least their native regional accent. This can refer to any accent, British is just a common example.\n\nHappens surprisingly often, either played straight or for laughs.\n\nAlmost the opposite of Ooh, Me Accent's Slipping, which is a slip from an assumed accent into a native one that is not deliberate.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HowsYourBritishAccent", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BionicWoman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/House", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Friends", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MasakoX", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheATeam", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheBestExoticMarigoldHotel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/InAmerica", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheIsland", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/EwanMcGregor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/LazerTeam", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/GavinFree", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheMerryWidow1934", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheParentTrap1998", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RockStar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ThirtyRock", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Alias", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DavidAnders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AlmostHuman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/KarlUrban", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BionicWoman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Blindspot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LukeMitchell", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BurnNotice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/GabrielleAnwar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JeffreyDonovan", "/pmwiki/pmwik